Georgia Recertifies Election Results, Affirming Biden’s VictoryIt was the latest blow to President Trump’s attempts to subvert the election. But battles over the process of voting in Georgia are likely to continue.

Republicans Make Clear Their Georgia Senate Strategy: Attack WarnockThe G.O.P. is focusing its attacks on the Rev. Raphael Warnock, portraying him as radical, which worked for Republicans in down-ballot races last month.

Trump Administration Passed on Chance to Secure More of Pfizer VaccineThe pharmaceutical company offered the government a chance to lock in additional supplies before its vaccine was proved effective in clinical trials.
Can Britain vaccinate tens of millions of people in a matter of months? Inoculations are to set begin Tuesday.
The Kremlin is offering free vaccines, but 59 percent of Russians say they don’t plan to get one.
